The paper proposes a deep learning framework for human action recognition using depth map sequences, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The use of ConvNets also suggests the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the generation of depth motion maps, which relates to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the rotation of depth data to handle view variant cases may be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
